&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Executive (Media Vertical/Eastern Region)- ServiceNow and AI Consulting Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Career&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Account Executive focused on Media, you will drive new business across broadcast, streaming, publishing, and entertainment companies navigating significant structural change. Content consolidation, M&amp;amp;A-driven integration debt, and the shift to direct-to-consumer models are creating real demand for workflow transformation. Your territory will be anchored on the East Coast, with target accounts including Comcast, NBCUniversal, Paramount, and AMC Networks -- companies managing complex operating environments where ServiceNow has a clear and defensible value story. If you understand how media companies operate, have existing relationships in the sector, and know how to position ServiceNow as a platform for operational scale, this role is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and execute territory plans across a defined set of media accounts, including near-term pipeline opportunities and longer-horizon relationship development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop relationships with key executive buyers -- CIO, COO, CFO, CDO -- particularly within companies undergoing post-merger integration or platform consolidation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead account strategy by mapping stakeholder relationships and coordinating a virtual team across Solutions Consultants, Solutions Specialists, Customer Success, and Alliance partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Position ServiceNow and AI-enabled workflow solutions in the context of media-specific operating challenges: rights management, production workflows, content supply chain, and workforce transformation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a healthy, qualified pipeline and deliver accurate biweekly forecasts to sales leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor competitive landscape, market conditions, and platform developments relevant to the media sector&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a sector SME, staying current on ServiceNow capabilities, industry trends, and client priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4 to 6 years selling ServiceNow solutions or competing SaaS platforms, with direct experience in media, entertainment, or adjacent sectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Existing relationships with technology buyers at broadcast, streaming, publishing, or entertainment companies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to sell consulting and advisory services, not just software licenses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with post-merger integration dynamics and how they drive technology consolidation decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with AI and agentic workflow positioning; ability to connect platform capabilities to operational outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of building pipeline from scratch, not inheriting it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable managing multiple concurrent sales cycles from initial qualification through close&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;East Coast based; willingness to travel to client sites as the coverage model requires&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education and Certifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BA/BS in Business, Technology, or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ServiceNow certifications preferred; industry-specific credentials a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
